  "text": "TypeMeta Re-export Chain Across Kubernetes Repositories:\n\n1. STARTING POINT - Pod Definition in kubernetes/kubernetes Staging:\n   - Repository: github.com/sg-evals/kubernetes--v1.32.0\n   - File: staging/src/k8s.io/api/core/v1/types.go\n   - Line: 5013\n   - Code: `type Pod struct { metav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"` ... }`\n   - Import Declaration (Line 21): `metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"`\n   - Import Alias: metav1\n   - Import Path: k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\n\n2. INTERMEDIATE - Re-export in kubernetes/api:\n   - Repository: github.com/sg-evals/api--v0.32.0 (mirrors staging/src/k8s.io/api)\n   - File: core/v1/types.go (corresponds to staging/src/k8s.io/api/core/v1/types.go in kubernetes/kubernetes)\n   - The kubernetes/api repository re-exports TypeMeta by importing metav1 from apimachinery and using it in its type definitions (Pod, PersistentVolume, PersistentVolumeClaim, etc.)\n   - No separate meta/v1 package exists in kubernetes/api; TypeMeta is accessed through the metav1 import from apimachinery\n\n3. ORIGINAL DEFINITION - TypeMeta in kubernetes/apimachinery:\n   - Repository: github.com/sg-evals/apimachinery--b2e9f88f\n   - File: pkg/apis/meta/v1/types.go\n   - Line: 42\n   - Struct Definition:\n     ```go\n     type TypeMeta struct {\n         // Kind is a string value representing the REST resource this object represents.\n         // Servers may infer this from the endpoint the client submits requests to.\n         // Cannot be updated.\n         // In CamelCase.\n         // More info: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md#types-kinds\n         // +optional\n         Kind string `json:\"kind,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,1,opt,name=kind\"` (Line 49)\n     \n         // APIVersion defines the versioned schema of this representation of an object.\n         // Servers should convert recognized schemas to the latest internal value, and\n         // may reject unrecognized values.\n         // More info: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md#resources\n         // +optional\n         APIVersion string `json:\"apiVersion,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,2,opt,name=apiVersion\"` (Line 56)\n     }\n     ```\n\nThe re-export chain shows that TypeMeta is defined once in kubernetes/apimachinery (pkg/apis/meta/v1/types.go) and is imported and used throughout kubernetes/api (core/v1 and other packages) by including the metav1 alias import of k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1. This centralized definition ensures consistency across all Kubernetes API types that need to embed metadata about their type and API version."
